Design rule: The horizontal tail should have an AR lower than the wing to ensure the tail stalls after the wing (no twist required on the tail).

The total pitching moment about the center of gravity (M_{cg}) is the sum of contributions from the wing, fuselage, propulsion, and tail:C_{M_{cg}} = C_{M_{ac,w}} + C_{M_{fus}} + C_{M_{prop}} + C_{M_{tail}}

Expanding:M_{cg} = M_{ac,w} + (x_{cg} - x_{ac}) L_w + M_{ac,t} - l_t L_t + M_F + M_P

The pitching moment coefficient about the c.g. is:C_{M_{cg}} = C_{M_{ac,w}} + \left(C_{L_W} + C_{L_t}\frac{S_t}{S_w}\right)\frac{(\bar{x}_{cg} - \bar{x}_{ac,w})}{\bar{c}} - C_{L_t} V_H + C_{M_{ac,t}} V_H \frac{\bar{c}_t}{l_t}

Where the horizontal tail volume coefficient is defined as:\boxed{V_H = \frac{S_t \cdot l_t}{S_w \cdot \bar{c}}}



Figure 3:Pitching moment contributions from the tail (empenage), fuselage, and wing. For static stability, the total aircraft curve must have a negative slope (\partial C_m / \partial \alpha < 0).

An aircraft is trimmed when it does not rotate about the c.g. in flight. Two conditions must be satisfied simultaneously:C_M = 0 \qquad \text{and} \qquad C_L = C_{L_{trim}} = \frac{2W}{\rho V_\infty^2 S_w}

Two unknowns must be solved: the angle of attack \alpha_{trim} and the elevator deflection \delta_{e_{trim}}.\alpha_{trim} = \frac{C_{M_0} C_{L_{\delta_e}} + C_{M_{\delta_e}} (C_{L_{trim}} - C_{L_0})}{C_{L_\alpha} C_{M_{\delta_e}} - C_{L_{\delta_e}} C_{M_\alpha}}\delta_{e_{trim}} = -\frac{C_{M_0} C_{L_\alpha} + C_{M_\alpha} (C_{L_{trim}} - C_{L_0})}{C_{L_\alpha} C_{M_{\delta_e}} - C_{L_{\delta_e}} C_{M_\alpha}}

Where the elevator effectiveness derivatives are:C_{L_{\delta_e}} = \frac{S_t}{S_w} C_{L_{\delta_{e_t}}}, \qquad C_{M_{\delta_e}} = C_{L_{\delta_{e_t}}} \frac{S_t}{S_w} (\bar{x}_{cg} - \bar{x}_{ac,w}) - C_{L_{\delta_{e_t}}} V_H
